{
  "message": "fix(fcp-conformance): regen capability-token expected_token_cbor for principal_zone claim\n\nCloses flywheel_connectors-lobrq.\n\nc828a3e7 (\"add principal zone access floor\") made CoseToken::sign\nsynthesize an additional CWT claim at positive key 3 (principal_zone,\nequal to the serialized zone_id) alongside the existing SCHEMA_VERSION\nsynthesis at key -16. The three CapabilityTokenGoldenVector entries had\nstale expected_token_cbor hex strings that encoded 9-entry payloads (a9)\n\u2014 the current path emits 10-entry payloads (aa/ac).\n\nRaw claims are unchanged: principal_zone is sign-time synthesis, not a\nCwtClaims field, so CwtClaims::to_cbor() still produces the previous\nbyte-for-byte output. Only the post-sign token_cbor fields needed regen.\n\nPatched:\n- vector_1_basic_capability: token_cbor now 10 entries, insert principal_zone\n  key 3 = \"z:work\" after key 1; new signature tail.\n- vector_2_with_holder_and_checkpoint: token_cbor now 12 entries, insert key\n  3 = \"z:private\"; new signature tail.\n- vector_3_multi_operation: token_cbor now 10 entries, insert key 3 =\n  \"z:public\"; new signature tail.\n\nDocstring on vector 1 updated to cite both regeneration commits (6df66c79\nand c828a3e7); vectors 2+3 get a short note.\n\nVerified green:\n- cargo test -p fcp-conformance --test serialization_roundtrip_conformance (10/10)\n- cargo test -p fcp-conformance --test negative_path_conformance (6/6, depends on golden vectors)\n- cargo test -p fcp-conformance --lib (947/947, includes vectors::capability::tests)\n\nCod_4 / SunnyMoose",
  "files": [
